                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24466",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The method still makes no sense in the final 1.6.0 release.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T04:05:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T04:05:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24468",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Reopened because the method still makes no sense in the final 1.6.0 release.\nThe description of the bugreport still applys.\n\nFirst of what the hell is $context?\nWhere does it come from?\nAnd why should it have input and id keys?\nAnd as reported the value of the $value parameter will be overwritten by the $context parameter input key entry.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T04:10:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T04:10:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24475",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Validators only need a value, but can also take an optional $context parameter; typically, this will be the set of values being validated, such as $_POST or $_GET. In Zend_Form, we pass the entire set of values being validated in the form to the $context parameter.\n\n$context is used to provide, well, context to the validator. In the case of a captcha, there are usually multiple values in the dataset that are used to identify and validate it: the \"id\" field is used so that Zend_Captcha knows which session namespace to look for the token in, and the \"input\" field is the actual user input that is being tested.\n\nWhile the logic may make no sense to *you*, it makes sense to those who have developed it, and, more importantly, it simply works.\n\nClosing the ticket again. Please do not re-open.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T05:47:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T05:47:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24483",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry but are you kidding me?\nThere are people who do not use Zend_Form at all.\n\nDid you have ever looked at the method?\nYou have to provide a context parameter, else the method tells you that it is missing the input or id key and the validation fails.\nSo when you have NO context it is not possible to validate the input.\n\nBesides that why do you have to provide the first parameter $value if it gets overwritten in any case by the value of the context parameter, see line 331 of Zend_Captcha_Word.\n\nSo, please make the method usable without the use of Zend_Form and its Zend_Captcha Element.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T06:02:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T06:02:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24484",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "in line 330 the content of $value is always overwritten by the context. you cant do anything about it :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T06:06:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T06:06:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24485",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "additionally $context is a mandatory parameter, if its not set the function returns false, line 326 to 329.\n\n    \tif (!isset($context[$name]['input'])) {\n    \t\t$this->_error(self::MISSING_VALUE);\n    \t\treturn false;\n    \t}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T06:11:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T06:11:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24497",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think I understand the issue.\n\nThe solution is to assume the value provided is an array, and contains both id and input elements within; that way, $context is not necessary.\n\nScheduling for next mini release (which, due to code freeze for 1.6.1, means 1.6.2). \n\nPlease note: this is NOT a show stopper. You can simply pass the context array when not using Zend_Form.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T10:33:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T10:33:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24501",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}The solution is to assume the value provided is an array, and contains both id and input elements within; that way, $context is not necessary.{quote}\nWhy not simply check if the $context is null and skip the checks because they are not needed when not using Zend_Form?\nBeside that why not even remove these checks completly and move them to Zend_Form.\n\n{quote}Please note: this is NOT a show stopper. You can simply pass the context array when not using Zend_Form.{quote}\nHow is this not a \"showstopper\"? Its nowhere documentated and it says nowhere how that array should be nested with what elements.\nBesides that the method looks unlogical in the first moment when you do not know about the senseless relation to Zend_Form.\n\nPassing the context array to the method is in no way logic. I guess normal user will fall into dispair when trying to use Zend_Image_Captcha.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ota",
                        "name": "ota",
                        "displayName": "Ota Mares",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T11:14:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T11:14:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
